{"cursor":"9689","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'tally' (or 'tally stick') was an ancient memory aid device used to record and\ndocument numbers, quantities, or even messages. Tally sticks first appear as\nanimal bones carved with notches, in the Upper Paleolithic; a notable example is\nthe Ishango Bone. Historical reference is made by Pliny the Elder (AD 23â79)\nabout the best wood to use for tallies, and by Marco Polo (1254â1324) who\nmentions the use of the tally in China. Tallies have been used for numerous\npurposes such as messaging and scheduling, and especially in financial and legal\ntransactions, to the point of being currency.\n","linknr":193,"url":"Tally_stick","recorded":1362673536,"links":26,"instances":["archaeology","united_kingdom"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Mnemonics","Writing systems","Mathematical tools"],"headings":["Kinds of tallies","See also","Notes","References","Further reading","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/SAM_PC_1_-_Tally_sticks_1_-_Overview.jpg/220px-SAM_PC_1_-_Tally_sticks_1_-_Overview.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["dolní_věstonice","archaeology"],["the_national_archives","united_kingdom"]],"members":["dolní_věstonice","the_national_archives"],"related":["Upper_Paleolithic","Ishango_Bone","Pliny_the_Elder","Marco_Polo","Currency","Swiss_Alpine_Museum","Prayer_beads","Ishango_bone","Bone_tool","Upper_Paleolithic","Fibula","Baboon","Fibula","Border_Cave","Lebombo_Mountains","Swaziland","Czechoslovakia","Dolní_Věstonice_(archaeology)","Moravia",